What you need to know:

The house, located on the side of a hill a kilometre from Maralal town in Samburu County, has a rich history.It is where Kenya's founding President, Mzee Jomo Kenyatta, was partially detained.Mzee Kenyatta lived in the house for one year after he was transferred from Lodwar.Mama Ngina Kenyatta and two of her daughters — Christine and Jane Njeri — also lived in the house with Mzee.